		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://martin.ankerl.com/2008/12/25/ripping-multilanguage-dvds-with-subtitles-using-only-mencoder/" rel="bookmark">Ripping Multilanguage DVDs with Subtitles using Mencoder</a></h1>
		<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="entry-date"><a href="http://martin.ankerl.com/2008/12/25/ripping-multilanguage-dvds-with-subtitles-using-only-mencoder/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2008-12-25T23:06:11+00:00">December 25, 2008</time></a></span> <span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://martin.ankerl.com/author/martinus/" rel="author">martinus</a></span></span>			<span class="comments-link"><a href="http://martin.ankerl.com/2008/12/25/ripping-multilanguage-dvds-with-subtitles-using-only-mencoder/#comments" title="Comment on Ripping Multilanguage DVDs with Subtitles using Mencoder">4 Comments</a></span>
					</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

		<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Yesterday at Christmas I got the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akira_Kurosawa">Akira Kurosawa</a> Samurai Edition, which is a 7 disc DVD set of his awesome movies. I am converting it into the best quality files currently possible: MKV as the container, x264 codec for the video, dual audio, and with subtitles. This is short Howto so that I won&#8217;t forget how <img src="http://martin.ankerl.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif?e08d73" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" /><br />
 <a href="http://martin.ankerl.com/2008/12/25/ripping-multilanguage-dvds-with-subtitles-using-only-mencoder/#more-185" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
